            	<h3><b>Decimal Number System</b></h3>
                <p>The Decimal number system is a base-10 number system and it is used by humans only and not understood by computers. Any numerical quantity can be represented using these 10 digits (0-9).</p>

                <h2><b>Conversion from Decimal to Binary</b></h2>
                <p>1. Divide the decimal number by 2.<br>
				2. Write the result below it and the remainder on the right.<br>
				3. Keep dividing the result by 2 until the result is equal to 0.<br>
				4. The remainders from bottom to top will be the answer. <br></p>

				<h2><b>Conversion from Decimal to Hexa-Decimal</b></h2>
				<p>1. Divide the decimal value by 16.<br>
				2. Write the remainder in Hexadecimal.<br>
				3. Repeat process mentioned above in 1 and 2 until the result is 0.</p>
                
